description:
Eurofins Scientific is an international life sciences company, providing a unique range of analytical testing services to clients across multiple industries, to make life and the environment safer, healthier and more sustainable. From the food you eat to the medicines you rely on, Eurofins works with the biggest companies in the world to ensure the products they supply are safe, their ingredients are authentic and labelling is accurate. Eurofins is a global leader in food, environmental, pharmaceutical and cosmetic product testing and in agroscience CRO services. It is also one of the global independent market leaders in certain testing and laboratory services for genomics, discovery pharmacology, forensics, CDMO, advanced material sciences and in the support of clinical studies.








 In over just 35 years, Eurofins has grown from one laboratory in Nantes, France to 62,000 staff across a network of over 1,000 independent companies in 61 countries, operating 900 laboratories. Performing over 450 million tests every year, Eurofins offers a portfolio of over 200,000 analytical methods to evaluate the safety, identity, composition, authenticity, origin, traceability and purity of biological substances and products, as well as providing innovative clinical diagnostic testing services, as one of the leading global emerging players in specialised clinical diagnostics testing.








 Eurofins is one of the fastest growing listed European companies with a listing on the French stock exchange since 1997\\.








 Eurofins IT Solutions India Pvt Ltd (EITSI) is a fully owned subsidiary of Eurofins and functions as a Global Software Delivery Center exclusively catering to Eurofins Global IT business needs. The code shipped out of EITSI impacts the global network of Eurofins labs and services.








 The primary focus at EITSI is to develop the next generation LIMS (Lab Information Management system), Customer portals, e\\-commerce solutions, ERP/CRM system, Mobile Apps \\& other B2B platforms for various Eurofins Laboratories and businesses. Young and dynamic, we have a rich culture and we offer fulfilling careers.



















**Job Description**

**TITLE:




 Senior AX Developer




 REPORTING TO: ERP Project Manager




 WORKING LOCATION: Bangalore (IN)




 OVERALL OBJECTIVES:**


 As a key member of the ERP team, the Senior Dynamics AX Developer will be responsible for grooming, designing, developing/customizing Microsoft AX based on the user requirements from the business stakeholders.








**ROLES \\& RESPONSIBILITIES:**


 Write, document, review, improve and troubleshoot code;




 Work closely with the functional team and the Solution Architect to understand and groom the user requirements, and design solutions based on AX and software engineer best practices;




 Prepare technical specifications, flow charts, software diagrams, and other technical documentation;




 Perform merge, build and deployment activities to promote the code to higher environments;




 Perform unit testing of all the customizations before promoting the code to higher environments and handing over to the quality assurance team.




 Support or execute data migrations activities using the Microsoft Data Migration Framework or other technologies;




 Perform AX Help Desk support, normally via Key Users, Business and Functional Analysts and coordination of related work across the different IT team members;




 Diagnose problems, recommends solutions, and determines whether program requirements have been met and/or must be improved;




 Contributes to the definition, improvement and strictly follow the best practices and procedures defined to ensure full compliance to the Eurofins and industry best practices.












**OTHER ASSIGNMENTS:**


 Assists in the training and development of technical support staff;




 Ensure follow\\-up to his/her Manager on a regular basis and as often as requested;




 Perform other responsibilities and duties as assigned.












**EVOLUTION**


 The Eurofins Pharma Discovery Services is a fairly new business line within the Organization, with an aggressive technological roadmap being implemented to support all the business processes worldwide.




 Being part of a fast\\-paced worldwide group, this position offers a great opportunity for personal and professional growth inside the business line and the rest of the Organization (may be subject to geographical relocation).








**PERFORMANCE APPRAISAL CRITERIA:**


 Eurofins has a strong focus on Performance Management system. This includes quarterly calibrations, half\\-yearly reviews, and annual reviews








**REQUIRED PROFILE:** 








**Experience:**



* At least 6 years of prior experience with software development, configuration and system support with Dynamics AX 2012;
* Relevant active technical participation in projects using Microsoft Dynamics AX 2012 R3 modules like General Ledger, Account Receivable, Accounts Payable, Sales \\& Marketing, Procurement \\& Sourcing;
* Minimum of 3 years of experience in developing reports using SSRS;
* Good exposure to .NET programming in the scope of interfaces;
* Installation and configuration of Dynamics AX 2012 R3 and its related components.
* Technical Skills:
* Very high proficiency in Dynamics AX development and customization aspects, including X\\+\\+ programing and AIF;
* Extended knowledge of Object\\-Oriented programming technologies, including X\\+\\+ and C\\#;
* Solid knowledge of Dynamics AX Architecture (layers, models, tiers, etc.);
* Deep understanding of RESTFul services, web services, WCF/AIF and service\\-oriented\\-architecture;
* Ability to troubleshoot existing and create new reports using SSRS;
* Good understanding of Microsoft Dynamics AX 2012 data structures;
* Understanding of Team Foundation System, proper code control, and branching of code.



**Travel:**


 Travels to Eurofins facilities mainly located in Europe and US are required (up to 15% of the time).











****Additional Information****

**Personal Skills:**



* Customer\\-service oriented with a problem\\-solving attitude;
* Strong attention to detail and accuracy is essential;
* Entrepreneurial thinking and flexibility to change;
* Very good English communication skills (concise writing and orally convincing);
* Structured and clear writing skills;
* Proven ability to solve complex business problems using analytical reasoning;
* Demonstrated positive attitude, self\\-motivated, team player.



**Required Qualifications:**



* MCA or Bachelors in Engineering, Computer Science or equivalent.



**PERFORMANCE APPRAISAL CRITERIA** 
 : Eurofins has a strong focus on Performance Management system. This includes quarterly calibrations, half\\-yearly reviews and annual reviews. The KPIs shall be set and may vary slightly between projects. These will be clearly communicated, documented during the first 30 days of your joining.
